The White House called for a thorough investigation into the poisoning of Ukrainian opposition leader Viktor Yushchenko with dioxin.
They emphasized support for democratic processes and fair elections.
Yushchenko accused the government of attempting to assassinate him, while his rival denied involvement.
Doctors confirmed dioxin poisoning, leading to disfigurement.
The US denied direct assistance to Yushchenko.
Prime Minister Yanukovych sought a probe into alleged US funding of Yushchenko's campaign.
The situation raised concerns and prompted calls for a comprehensive inquiry into the disturbing incident.
